task.summary:
Added and played with learnclojure.clj a little bit.
Q: Why does the print-and-say-hello function print 2 spaces between 'to' and the name it's saying hello to when it prints?
Created helloworld.clj! Yay! My first complete Clojure program!

Took out the docstring of helloworld.clj and discovered that the IDE will automatically push semicolons (comments) out to a certain column if it's in the same line as a statement. I wonder if that can be controlled or configured?
Trying to add an overloaded functionality to the helloworld function; there does not appear to be any output.
Exploring the language a little more... The sadbox is a sandbox-type-thing.
learnclojure still gets a 'cannot be resolved' error on the difference operation on line 296. Not sure why - it runs and prints the operation and its result just fine.
added loops with a while loop example - has the mysterious atom data type as well.
added the doseq statement to the loops example namespace
Added dotimes and loop loop statements to the loop example file.
Started looking at decision statements (if and the like). Small change to simplify the output in loops.clj.
added some things to Example3 in decisions.clj.
